suspect capital assets will be harder to maintain in the future. if you imagine the most powerful capital assets are rivalrous monopolistic goods like land or equity in Meta

Land may be worth less if you can build new gleaming cities in the middle of Oklahoma, though it’s no guarantee. Land may also become increasingly valuable as it has for the last many decades. It has always been the case that land should have special high taxes although no one listens 

Public equities compete on data/knowledge moats and social network moats both of which may be competed away with increasing intelligence. Compute is undifferentiated commodity unless there is hyperscale extreme concentration. 

It’s sort of like how hedge funds and trading funds, which happen to be some of the most optimized parts of the economy, struggle to maintain any lasting lead over one another. The total capitalization of trading firms is relatively small compared to the assets they manage. Perhaps something similar happens to the whole economy
